\'d3 \'c4\'e6\'e5\'e9\'ed (\'e3\'ee\'eb\'f3\'e1\'e0\'ff \'ec\'e0\'e9\'ea\'e0) \'e1\'fb\'eb \'ea\'ee\'f2\'e5\'ed\'ea\'ee\'ea. \'ce\'ed\'e0 \'ee\'f7\'e5\'ed\'fc \'eb\'fe\'e1\'e8\'eb\'e0 \'e5\'e3\'ee. \'ca\'e0\'e6\'e4\'fb\'e9 \'e4\'e5\'ed\'fc \'ea\'ee\'f0\'ec\'e8\'eb\'e0 \'e5\'e3\'ee \'e2\'ea\'f3\'f1\'ed\'ee\'e9 \'e5\'e4\'ee\'e9 \'e8 \'e8\'e3\'f0\'e0\'eb\'e0 \'f1 \'ed\'e8\'ec. \par
\par
\f1\lang1033 ===================================\par
\f0\lang1049\'c2 \'ee\'e4\'ed\'ee\'ec \'e3\'ee\'f0\'ee\'e4\'e5 \'e6\'e8\'eb\'e8 \'e4\'e2\'e5 \'ec\'e0\'eb\'e5\'ed\'fc\'ea\'e8\'e5 \'e4\'e5\'e2\'ee\'f7\'ea\'e8, \f1\lang1033 Julie and Jane\f0\lang1049 .\par
\'c3\'ee\'f1\'f2\'e8 \'e4\'f0\'f3\'e3 \'e4\'f0\'f3\'e3\'f3, \'e8\'e3\'f0\'e0\'eb\'e8.\par
\f1\lang1033\par
\par
\par
===================================\f0\lang1049\par
\par
\par
\f1\lang1033 There were two little girls, Julie and Jane, living in the village.\f0\lang1049\par
\f1\lang1033 Despite that they were neighbors they did not like each other very much.\par
Julie had a kitten named Simba.\par
Simba had its own cozy box where it loved to sleep.\par
\f0\lang1049\par
\f1\lang1033 Once Simba did what made the girls good friends.\par
\f0\lang1049\par
Julie went to school\f1\lang1033  \f0\lang1049 as usual.\par
\f1\lang1033 Her kitten was home alone and felt bored. Simba walking from one room to another saw a butterfly. found it very interesting and began to play.\par
butterfly flew outside through an open window the kitten followed.\par
T\f0\lang1049 he kitten, playing with a butterfly, step by step, went far away from home.\par
1. \f1\lang1033 When Julie came back home, she could not find the kitten anywhere.\par
\f0\lang1049 2. \f1\lang1033 When Julie came back home, she found that the kitten was not anywhere.\par
\f0\lang1049 3. \f1\lang1033 When Julie got home, she found that the kitten was nowhere to be found.\par
usually the pet would meet her so it was strange for her.\par
After unsuccessful attempts to find her pet, Julie took her bicycle and went outside hoping to find her kitten.\par
\par
The girl checked every bush calling for Simba.\par
\par
When Julie was riding her bicycle she ran over a stone lying ahead and hurt her leg.\par
When Julie was riding the bicycle, she fell and hurt her leg. Crying she called Jane with her phone. Happily, Jane was not far and came to Julie in a minute.\par
Julie's parents were at their jobs and could not help their daughter. Jane helped Julie to get to her home and said: "Stay here, I am going to try to find Simba".\par
When Julie's parents returned home in the evening, they handled (took care of) Julie's leg. Then they heard that someone knocked the door. Opened it they saw the girl with the kitten. Since the time the girls became good friends. (Since then, the girls have become good friends.)\par
\par
Years later, when the girl\f2\lang1055 s\f1\lang1033  grew up, their friendship were put to the test.\par
#Over the years, as the girls grew up, their friendship was tested.\par
\par
Jane met Jehovah's Witnesses and began studying the Bible. When Julie learned it, she got anxious about her childhood friend. The thing was that Julie heard something bad regarding Witnesses.\par
Jane had been studying for a couple of months when Julie finally said "Jane! You must choose either me or Jehovah!" and threw the photo taken when they were children on the ground. \par
Jane said Julie that the good time is going to be on the earth and explained her why she believed it. And thus she can be confident that her loved grandma whom Julie loved will be ressurected. Julie was so amazed and excited that began to cry. So they talked each other for an hour about God's promises.\par
Julie and Jane both are pioneers now, and they are very close.\par
\par
